  <how_to_use_section>
    <how_to_use>
      <how_to_use_steps>
        <step>Open the Visual Studio solution file.</step>
        <step>Build the solution.</step>
        <step>Start ArcGlobe.</step>
        <step>On the Customize dialog box, choose the Add-In Controls category.</step>
        <step>On the Command Items pane, drag the Camera flyby from path onto a toolbar.</step>
        <step>To move the globe camera along a path, add a line feature dataset in the globe session. Also, select a line feature using the "Select features" tool. The selected line is the one along which the globe camera will be animated. </step>
        <step>Choose the tool.</step>
        <step>Choose the options on the Camera Flyby From Path form.</step>
        <step>On running the tool, a Globe Camera track gets added to the globe.</step>
        <step>An animation is created, which can then be played by clicking Customize, Toolbars, and Animation to open the Animation Toolbar and then clicking on “Open Animation Controls” command</step>
      </how_to_use_steps>
    </how_to_use>
